  "riddle": "1. Pinpoint the assembly constituency in Punjab that has a current representative elected in a year waiting to be unveiled. What year was it?\n\n2. This constituency lies within a city known for its geographical coordinates—what are their precise values?\n\n3. Amongst the features of this place, how high does it rise above the sea level, in meters?\n\n4. Scattered through and around this area, how many hospitals can you find nearby?\n\n5. Calculate the difference between the elevation you discovered in clue 3 and the count of hospitals from clue 4. What is the absolute value of that difference?\n\n6. In the landscape where you tread, how many people inhabit the vast nation belonging to this region?\n\n7. The legislative body framework has a current assembly with some members on the treasury benches. How many members from a certain party sit there?\n\n8. A number you found in clue 7 is significant—what is the next prime number after that figure?\n\n9. Returning to the vast nation, how many people call it home once more?\n\n10. Discover the duration, in years, that a member serves in the assembly. What is that term length?\n\n11. To understand the influence of their tenure, unveil the number of divisors of the term length from clue 10.\n\n12. Follow the path back to the elevation you unearthed in clue 3 and the term duration from clue 10. Now, compute the digital root of the sum of those two numbers increased by five. What is the result? \n\nRemember, your final answer will be a single digit derived from your computations!",
